@page "/"

<PageTitle>NYC DOB Job Filings Explorer</PageTitle>

<div class="px-4 py-5 my-5 text-center">
    <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold">NYC DOB Job Application Filings Explorer</h1>
    <div class="col-lg-6 mx-auto">
        <p class="lead mb-4">
            Explore NYC Department of Buildings job application filings with dynamic columns, smart filters, and progressive loading.
        </p>
        <div class="d-grid gap-2 d-sm-flex justify-content-sm-center">
            <a href="job-filings" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg px-4 gap-3">Explore Job Filings</a>
            <a href="column-preferences" class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-lg px-4">Customize Columns</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
        <div class="card h-100">
            <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
                <h5 class="mb-0">Dynamic Columns</h5>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>Configure which columns to display, their order, and save your preferences. Customization is fully metadata-driven.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Show/hide columns</li>
                    <li>Reorder columns</li>
                    <li>Pin important columns</li>
                    <li>Saved per user</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
        <div class="card h-100">
            <div class="card-header bg-success text-white">
                <h5 class="mb-0">Smart Filter Chips</h5>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>Create and combine filters to narrow your search. Filter chips apply to both data grid and chart visualizations.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Filter by date, borough, job type</li>
                    <li>Numeric comparisons</li>
                    <li>Save filter combinations</li>
                    <li>Apply to grid and charts</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
        <div class="card h-100">
            <div class="card-header bg-info text-dark">
                <h5 class="mb-0">Progressive Loading</h5>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>Handle large result sets efficiently with background loading and progress tracking.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>First 1,000 rows load immediately</li>
                    <li>Background loading of more data</li>
                    <li>Progress indicator</li>
                    <li>Cancellable operations</li>
                    <li>Optimized column loading</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="alert alert-info mt-4">
    <h4>Dataset Information</h4>
    <p>This application uses the <strong>NYC DOB Job Application Filings</strong> dataset from NYC Open Data.</p>
    <p>The dataset contains approximately 2.7 million records of job filings submitted to the Department of Buildings since 2000.</p>
    <a href="https://data.cityofnewyork.us/Housing-Development/DOB-Job-Application-Filings/ic3t-wcy2/about_data" target="_blank" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-info">
        Learn More About the Dataset
    </a>
</div>
